  "texts": [
    "However, if the environment slightly changes, e.g., a static obstacle is shifted, Dyna-Q requires many training steps to update the model and often follows a suboptimal policy until the model is updated [6].In this work, we propose a provably safe shield to verify model-based RL agents online.",
    "We introduce a local Qfunction that includes the effect of the safety shield for multiple future time steps, which leads to a more performant action selection, especially under distribution shifts, which could originate from a sim-to-real gap of the environment model.",
    "Our main contributions are:• We integrate a multi-step safety shield into the modelbased RL algorithm Dyna-Q; • We derive the assumptions necessary to ensure optimality of our approach; • We compare our approach to state-of-the-art baselines to empirically investigate the prediction parameters of our safety shield.",
